{
  "text": "In our representation formulas are prefixed by a number that represents possible worlds in the model (similar to [CITATION_1] Chapter 8] ). Formulas are also prefixed by finite sequences of announcements corresponding to successive model restrictions. Given a finite sequence of formulas \u03c8 k = (\u03c8 1 . . . \u03c8 k ), for each 1 \u2264 i \u2264 k, the sequence (\u03c8 1 . . . \u03c8 i ) is noted \u03c8 i whereas \u03c8 0 = denotes the empty sequence. In addition, we write M |\u03c8 k for M |\u03c8 1 | . . . |\u03c8 k .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "118574141"
  },
